a reprogramming machine.win this paper a description is given of a modelprogramming system which is directed by a programming language and has a library for storing the user's items. rules are given for transforming programs written in the language and for rearranging the items in thelibrary so that they share their common parts.  some speculations are made about how the mechanicaldetection of common parts or patterns of library items could help a user to solve his problems, and aboutthe relationships between the behavior of the reprogramming machine and human intelligent behavior.cacm february, burge, w. h.ca jb march ,   : pm